{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 has been assigned gate A1. Report wheels chocks readiness at the gate.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-5.4-mini", #"gpt-4o", # "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", #"claude-sonnet-4-6", #
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "wheels_chocks_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am in charge of wheels chocks at the gate.
I set up wheels chocks and report wheels chocks readiness status when user inquires.
I am ALWAYS relevant when asked about wheels chocks readiness or any ground
services readiness check that includes wheels chocks. I never refuse based
on missing or null status fields.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },          
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },   
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },                 
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of wheels chocks at the gate.
You are ALWAYS relevant when asked about wheels chocks readiness or any
ground services readiness check. Never refuse based on missing or null fields.
When you receive an inquiry, proceed as follows:
1. Read the inquiry. Any inquiry about ground services readiness, wheels chocks
   readiness status, or wheels chocks installation/connection is relevant to you.
   Only reply not relevant if the inquiry is entirely unrelated to wheels chocks
   or ground services (e.g. a question about catering or passengers).
2. If the inquiry is about wheels chocks readiness status,
    a. call your tool to inquire about wheels chocks readiness status as wheels_chocks_readiness_status,
    b. store the returned wheels_chocks_readiness_status,
    c. report its value back to user.
3. Call TrackerAPI and log all available parameters.
    a. wait for its response,
    b. store all available parameters.
4. Provide the wheels chocks readiness status summary as:
    ***********************************************
    * Summary of aircraft wheels chocks readiness *
    ***********************************************
    ** aircraft_type **: [aircraft_type]
    ** flight_number **: [flight_number]
    ** gate_id **: [gate_id]
    ** wheels chocks readiness status **: [wheels_chocks_readiness_status]
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks. 
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_number": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_number": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_number": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "aircraft_type": true
                        "flight_number": true
                        "gate_id": true 
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["wheels_chocks_setup","TrackerAPI"]
        },

        {
            "name": "wheels_chocks_setup",
            "function": {
                "description": """
This agent report the status of wheels chocks readiness at the gate. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },           
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },   
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },     
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_setup.aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_setup.wheels_chocks_setup" 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },   
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },      
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },       
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_setup.aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_setup.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}


# engines_stop_status` and `wheels_chucks_installation_status` referenced; neither is